        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:31PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Robbinsville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Robbinsville, Town Of Santeetlah, Fontana Lake, Smoky
Mountains-Fontana Area, Lake Santeetlah, Wesser, Stecoah, Almond,
Nantahala, and Cheoah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
